80.1	Amory_Lovins	Amory Lovins	Amory Bloch Lovins (born November 13, 1947) is an American physicist, environmental scientist, writer, and Chairman/Chief Scientist of the Rocky Mountain Institute. He has worked in the field of energy policy and related areas for four decades. Harvard University-educated, he was named by Time magazine one of the World's 100 most influential people in 2009.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Amory_Lovins.jpg/220px-Amory_Lovins.jpg
